The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques to solve the extreme multi-label text classification (XMC) problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a scalable solution to finetune BERT models, which is related to large-scale ML, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The XMC problem involves tagging input text with the most relevant labels from an extremely large set, which is related to information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR another possible category. The paper also uses pre-trained language representation models such as BERT, which is related to artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with text classification, which is related to computer vision (CV), making cs.CV another possible category.
